69 /// Canonicalize metadata arguments to intrinsics. ----
70 /// ----
71 /// To support bitcode upgrades (and assembly semantic sugar) for \a ----
72 /// MetadataAsValue, we need to canonicalize certain metadata. ----
73 /// ----
74 /// - nullptr is replaced by an empty MDNode. ----
75 /// - An MDNode with a single null operand is replaced by an empty MDNode. ----
76 /// - An MDNode whose only operand is a \a ConstantAsMetadata gets skipped. ----
77 /// ----
78 /// This maintains readability of bitcode from when metadata was a type of ----
79 /// value, and these bridges were unnecessary. ----
80 static Metadata *canonicalizeMetadataForValue(LLVMContext &Context, 15 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
81 Metadata *MD) { ----
82 if (!MD) 15 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
83 // !{} ----
84 return MDNode::get(Context, std::nullopt); 0
85 ----
86 // Return early if this isn't a single-operand MDNode. ----
87 auto *N = dyn_cast(MD); 15 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
88 if (!N || N->getNumOperands() != 1) 15 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
89 return MD; 15 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
90 ----
91 if (!N->getOperand(0)) 0
92 // !{} ----
93 return MDNode::get(Context, std::nullopt); 0
94 ----
95 if (auto *C = dyn_cast(N->getOperand(0))) 0
96 // Look through the MDNode. ----
97 return C; 0
98 ----
99 return MD; 0
100 } ----

433 MD->replaceAllUsesWith(nullptr); 11 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll

437 void ValueAsMetadata::handleRAUW(Value *From, Value *To) { 3 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
438 assert(From && "Expected valid value"); 3 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
439 assert(To && "Expected valid value"); 3 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
440 assert(From != To && "Expected changed value"); 3 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
441 assert(From->getType() == To->getType() && "Unexpected type change"); 3 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
442 ----
443 LLVMContext &Context = From->getType()->getContext(); 3 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
444 auto &Store = Context.pImpl->ValuesAsMetadata; 3 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
445 auto I = Store.find(From); 3 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
446 if (I == Store.end()) { 3 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
447 assert(!From->IsUsedByMD && "Expected From not to be used by metadata"); 0
448 return; 3 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
449 } ----
450 ----
451 // Remove old entry from the map. ----
452 assert(From->IsUsedByMD && "Expected From to be used by metadata"); 3 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
453 From->IsUsedByMD = false; 3 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
454 ValueAsMetadata *MD = I->second; 3 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
455 assert(MD && "Expected valid metadata"); 3 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
456 assert(MD->getValue() == From && "Expected valid mapping"); 3 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
457 Store.erase(I); 3 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
458 ----
459 if (isa(MD)) { 3 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
460 if (auto *C = dyn_cast(To)) { 3 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
461 // Local became a constant. ----
462 MD->replaceAllUsesWith(ConstantAsMetadata::get(C)); 3 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
463 delete MD; 3 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
464 return; 3 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
465 } ----
466 if (getLocalFunctionMetadata(From) && getLocalFunctionMetadata(To) && 0
467 getLocalFunctionMetadata(From) != getLocalFunctionMetadata(To)) { 0
468 // DISubprogram changed. ----
469 MD->replaceAllUsesWith(nullptr); 0
470 delete MD; 0
471 return; 0
472 } ----
473 } else if (!isa(To)) { 0
474 // Changed to function-local value. ----
475 MD->replaceAllUsesWith(nullptr); 0
476 delete MD; 0
477 return; 0
478 } ----
479 ----
480 auto *&Entry = Store[To]; 0
481 if (Entry) { 0
482 // The target already exists. ----
483 MD->replaceAllUsesWith(Entry); 0
484 delete MD; 0
485 return; 0
486 } ----
487 ----
488 // Update MD in place (and update the map entry). ----
489 assert(!To->IsUsedByMD && "Expected this to be the only metadata use"); 0
490 To->IsUsedByMD = true; 0
491 MD->V = To; 0
492 Entry = MD; 0
493 } ----

604 void MDNode::Header::resize(size_t NumOps) { 0
605 assert(IsResizable && "Node is not resizable"); 0
606 if (operands().size() == NumOps) 0
607 return; 0
608 ----
609 if (IsLarge) 0
610 getLarge().resize(NumOps); 0
611 else if (NumOps <= SmallSize) 0
612 resizeSmall(NumOps); 0
613 else ----
614 resizeSmallToLarge(NumOps); 0
615 } ----
616 ----
617 void MDNode::Header::resizeSmall(size_t NumOps) { 0
618 assert(!IsLarge && "Expected a small MDNode"); 0
619 assert(NumOps <= SmallSize && "NumOps too large for small resize"); 0
620 ----
621 MutableArrayRef ExistingOps = operands(); 0
622 assert(NumOps != ExistingOps.size() && "Expected a different size"); 0
623 ----
624 int NumNew = (int)NumOps - (int)ExistingOps.size(); 0
625 MDOperand *O = ExistingOps.end(); 0
626 for (int I = 0, E = NumNew; I < E; ++I) 0
627 (O++)->reset(); 0
628 for (int I = 0, E = NumNew; I > E; --I) 0
629 (--O)->reset(); 0
630 SmallNumOps = NumOps; 0
631 assert(O == operands().end() && "Operands not (un)initialized until the end"); 0
632 } 0
633 ----
634 void MDNode::Header::resizeSmallToLarge(size_t NumOps) { 0
635 assert(!IsLarge && "Expected a small MDNode"); 0
636 assert(NumOps > SmallSize && "Expected NumOps to be larger than allocation"); 0
637 LargeStorageVector NewOps; 0
638 NewOps.resize(NumOps); 0
639 llvm::move(operands(), NewOps.begin()); 0
640 resizeSmall(0); 0
641 new (getLargePtr()) LargeStorageVector(std::move(NewOps)); 0
642 IsLarge = true; 0
643 } 0

809 void MDNode::handleChangedOperand(void *Ref, Metadata *New) { 5 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
810 unsigned Op = static_cast(Ref) - op_begin(); 5 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
811 assert(Op < getNumOperands() && "Expected valid operand"); 5 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
812 ----
813 if (!isUniqued()) { 5 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
814 // This node is not uniqued. Just set the operand and be done with it. ----
815 setOperand(Op, New); 0
816 return; 5 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
817 } ----
818 ----
819 // This node is uniqued. ----
820 eraseFromStore(); 5 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
821 ----
822 Metadata *Old = getOperand(Op); 5 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
823 setOperand(Op, New); 5 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
824 ----
825 // Drop uniquing for self-reference cycles and deleted constants. ----
826 if (New == this || (!New && Old && isa(Old))) { 5 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
827 if (!isResolved()) 0
828 resolve(); 0
829 storeDistinctInContext(); 0
830 return; 0
831 } ----
832 ----
833 // Re-unique the node. ----
834 auto *Uniqued = uniquify(); 5 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
835 if (Uniqued == this) { 5 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
836 if (!isResolved()) 5 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
837 resolveAfterOperandChange(Old, New); 5 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
838 return; 5 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
839 } ----
840 ----
841 // Collision. ----
842 if (!isResolved()) { 0
843 // Still unresolved, so RAUW. ----
844 // ----
845 // First, clear out all operands to prevent any recursion (similar to ----
846 // dropAllReferences(), but we still need the use-list). ----
847 for (unsigned O = 0, E = getNumOperands(); O != E; ++O) 0
848 setOperand(O, nullptr); 0
849 if (Context.hasReplaceableUses()) 0
850 Context.getReplaceableUses()->replaceAllUsesWith(Uniqued); 0
851 deleteAsSubclass(); 0
852 return; 0
853 } ----
854 ----
855 // Store in non-uniqued form if RAUW isn't possible. ----
856 storeDistinctInContext(); 0
857 } ----

899 #define HANDLE_MDNODE_LEAF_UNIQUABLE(CLASS) \ ----

901 CLASS *SubclassThis = cast(this); \ ----
902 std::integral_constant::value> \ ----
903 ShouldRecalculateHash; \ ----

906 } ----

908 } ----

987 /// Get a node or a self-reference that looks like it. ----
988 /// ----
989 /// Special handling for finding self-references, for use by \a ----
990 /// MDNode::concatenate() and \a MDNode::intersect() to maintain behaviour from ----
991 /// when self-referencing nodes were still uniqued. If the first operand has ----
992 /// the same operands as \c Ops, return the first operand instead. ----
993 static MDNode *getOrSelfReference(LLVMContext &Context, 0
994 ArrayRef Ops) { ----
995 if (!Ops.empty()) 0
996 if (MDNode *N = dyn_cast_or_null(Ops[0])) 0
997 if (N->getNumOperands() == Ops.size() && N == N->getOperand(0)) { 0
998 for (unsigned I = 1, E = Ops.size(); I != E; ++I) 0
999 if (Ops[I] != N->getOperand(I)) 0
1000 return MDNode::get(Context, Ops); 0
1001 return N; 0
1002 } ----
1003 ----
1004 return MDNode::get(Context, Ops); 0
1005 } ----
1006 ----
1007 MDNode *MDNode::concatenate(MDNode *A, MDNode *B) { 0
1008 if (!A) 0
1009 return B; 0
1010 if (!B) 0
1011 return A; 0
1012 ----
1013 SmallSetVector MDs(A->op_begin(), A->op_end()); 0
1014 MDs.insert(B->op_begin(), B->op_end()); 0
1015 ----
1016 // FIXME: This preserves long-standing behaviour, but is it really the right ----
1017 // behaviour? Or was that an unintended side-effect of node uniquing? ----
1018 return getOrSelfReference(A->getContext(), MDs.getArrayRef()); 0
1019 } 0
1020 ----
1021 MDNode *MDNode::intersect(MDNode *A, MDNode *B) { 0
1022 if (!A || !B) 0
1023 return nullptr; 0
1024 ----
1025 SmallSetVector MDs(A->op_begin(), A->op_end()); 0
1026 SmallPtrSet BSet(B->op_begin(), B->op_end()); 0
1027 MDs.remove_if([&](Metadata *MD) { return !BSet.count(MD); }); 0
1028 ----
1029 // FIXME: This preserves long-standing behaviour, but is it really the right ----
1030 // behaviour? Or was that an unintended side-effect of node uniquing? ----
1031 return getOrSelfReference(A->getContext(), MDs.getArrayRef()); 0
1032 } 0

1034 MDNode *MDNode::getMostGenericAliasScope(MDNode *A, MDNode *B) { 0
1035 if (!A || !B) 0
1036 return nullptr; 0
1037 ----
1038 // Take the intersection of domains then union the scopes ----
1039 // within those domains ----
1040 SmallPtrSet ADomains; 0
1041 SmallPtrSet IntersectDomains; 0
1042 SmallSetVector MDs; 0
1043 for (const MDOperand &MDOp : A->operands()) 0
1044 if (const MDNode *NAMD = dyn_cast(MDOp)) 0
1045 if (const MDNode *Domain = AliasScopeNode(NAMD).getDomain()) 0
1046 ADomains.insert(Domain); 0
1047 ----
1048 for (const MDOperand &MDOp : B->operands()) 0
1049 if (const MDNode *NAMD = dyn_cast(MDOp)) 0
1050 if (const MDNode *Domain = AliasScopeNode(NAMD).getDomain()) 0
1051 if (ADomains.contains(Domain)) { 0
1052 IntersectDomains.insert(Domain); 0
1053 MDs.insert(MDOp); 0
1054 } ----
1055 ----
1056 for (const MDOperand &MDOp : A->operands()) 0
1057 if (const MDNode *NAMD = dyn_cast(MDOp)) 0
1058 if (const MDNode *Domain = AliasScopeNode(NAMD).getDomain()) 0
1059 if (IntersectDomains.contains(Domain)) 0
1060 MDs.insert(MDOp); 0
1061 ----
1062 return MDs.empty() ? nullptr 0
1063 : getOrSelfReference(A->getContext(), MDs.getArrayRef()); 0
1064 } 0

1077 // Call instructions with branch weights are only used in SamplePGO as ----
1078 // documented in ----
1079 /// https://llvm.org/docs/BranchWeightMetadata.html#callinst). ----
1080 MDNode *MDNode::mergeDirectCallProfMetadata(MDNode *A, MDNode *B, 0
1081 const Instruction *AInstr, ----
1082 const Instruction *BInstr) { ----
1083 assert(A && B && AInstr && BInstr && "Caller should guarantee"); 0
1084 auto &Ctx = AInstr->getContext(); 0
1085 MDBuilder MDHelper(Ctx); 0
1086 ----
1087 // LLVM IR verifier verifies !prof metadata has at least 2 operands. ----
1088 assert(A->getNumOperands() >= 2 && B->getNumOperands() >= 2 && 0
1089 "!prof annotations should have no less than 2 operands"); ----
1090 MDString *AMDS = dyn_cast(A->getOperand(0)); 0
1091 MDString *BMDS = dyn_cast(B->getOperand(0)); 0
1092 // LLVM IR verfier verifies first operand is MDString. ----
1093 assert(AMDS != nullptr && BMDS != nullptr && 0
1094 "first operand should be a non-null MDString"); ----
1095 StringRef AProfName = AMDS->getString(); 0
1096 StringRef BProfName = BMDS->getString(); 0
1097 if (AProfName.equals("branch_weights") && 0
1098 BProfName.equals("branch_weights")) { 0
1099 ConstantInt *AInstrWeight = ----
1100 mdconst::dyn_extract(A->getOperand(1)); 0
1101 ConstantInt *BInstrWeight = ----
1102 mdconst::dyn_extract(B->getOperand(1)); 0
1103 assert(AInstrWeight && BInstrWeight && "verified by LLVM verifier"); 0
1104 return MDNode::get(Ctx, 0
1105 {MDHelper.createString("branch_weights"), 0
1106 MDHelper.createConstant(ConstantInt::get( 0
1107 Type::getInt64Ty(Ctx), ----
1108 SaturatingAdd(AInstrWeight->getZExtValue(), ----
1109 BInstrWeight->getZExtValue())))}); 0
1110 } ----
1111 return nullptr; 0
1112 } ----

1114 // Pass in both instructions and nodes. Instruction information (e.g., ----
1115 // instruction type) helps interpret profiles and make implementation clearer. ----
1116 MDNode *MDNode::getMergedProfMetadata(MDNode *A, MDNode *B, 0
1117 const Instruction *AInstr, ----
1118 const Instruction *BInstr) { ----
1119 if (!(A && B)) { 0
1120 return A ? A : B; 0
1121 } ----

1126 "Caller should guarantee"); ----

1129 const CallInst *BCall = dyn_cast(BInstr); 0
1130 ----

1132 if (ACall && BCall && ACall->getCalledFunction() && 0

1141 static bool isContiguous(const ConstantRange &A, const ConstantRange &B) { 0
1142 return A.getUpper() == B.getLower() || A.getLower() == B.getUpper(); 0
1143 } ----
1144 ----
1145 static bool canBeMerged(const ConstantRange &A, const ConstantRange &B) { 0
1146 return !A.intersectWith(B).isEmptySet() || isContiguous(A, B); 0
1147 } ----
1148 ----
1149 static bool tryMergeRange(SmallVectorImpl &EndPoints, 0
1150 ConstantInt *Low, ConstantInt *High) { ----
1151 ConstantRange NewRange(Low->getValue(), High->getValue()); 0
1152 unsigned Size = EndPoints.size(); 0
1153 APInt LB = EndPoints[Size - 2]->getValue(); 0
1154 APInt LE = EndPoints[Size - 1]->getValue(); 0
1155 ConstantRange LastRange(LB, LE); 0
1156 if (canBeMerged(NewRange, LastRange)) { 0
1157 ConstantRange Union = LastRange.unionWith(NewRange); 0
1158 Type *Ty = High->getType(); 0
1159 EndPoints[Size - 2] = 0
1160 cast(ConstantInt::get(Ty, Union.getLower())); 0
1161 EndPoints[Size - 1] = 0
1162 cast(ConstantInt::get(Ty, Union.getUpper())); 0
1163 return true; 0
1164 } 0
1165 return false; 0
1166 } 0
1167 ----
1168 static void addRange(SmallVectorImpl &EndPoints, 0
1169 ConstantInt *Low, ConstantInt *High) { ----
1170 if (!EndPoints.empty()) 0
1171 if (tryMergeRange(EndPoints, Low, High)) 0
1172 return; 0
1173 ----
1174 EndPoints.push_back(Low); 0
1175 EndPoints.push_back(High); 0
1176 } ----
1177 ----
1178 MDNode *MDNode::getMostGenericRange(MDNode *A, MDNode *B) { 0
1179 // Given two ranges, we want to compute the union of the ranges. This ----
1180 // is slightly complicated by having to combine the intervals and merge ----
1181 // the ones that overlap. ----
1182 ----
1183 if (!A || !B) 0
1184 return nullptr; 0
1185 ----
1186 if (A == B) 0
1187 return A; 0
1188 ----
1189 // First, walk both lists in order of the lower boundary of each interval. ----
1190 // At each step, try to merge the new interval to the last one we adedd. ----
1191 SmallVector EndPoints; 0
1192 int AI = 0; 0
1193 int BI = 0; 0
1194 int AN = A->getNumOperands() / 2; 0
1195 int BN = B->getNumOperands() / 2; 0
1196 while (AI < AN && BI < BN) { 0
1197 ConstantInt *ALow = mdconst::extract(A->getOperand(2 * AI)); 0
1198 ConstantInt *BLow = mdconst::extract(B->getOperand(2 * BI)); 0
1199 ----
1200 if (ALow->getValue().slt(BLow->getValue())) { 0
1201 addRange(EndPoints, ALow, 0
1202 mdconst::extract(A->getOperand(2 * AI + 1))); 0
1203 ++AI; 0
1204 } else { ----
1205 addRange(EndPoints, BLow, 0
1206 mdconst::extract(B->getOperand(2 * BI + 1))); 0
1207 ++BI; 0
1208 } ----
1209 } ----
1210 while (AI < AN) { 0
1211 addRange(EndPoints, mdconst::extract(A->getOperand(2 * AI)), 0
1212 mdconst::extract(A->getOperand(2 * AI + 1))); 0
1213 ++AI; 0
1214 } ----
1215 while (BI < BN) { 0
1216 addRange(EndPoints, mdconst::extract(B->getOperand(2 * BI)), 0
1217 mdconst::extract(B->getOperand(2 * BI + 1))); 0
1218 ++BI; 0
1219 } ----
1220 ----
1221 // If we have more than 2 ranges (4 endpoints) we have to try to merge ----
1222 // the last and first ones. ----
1223 unsigned Size = EndPoints.size(); 0
1224 if (Size > 4) { 0
1225 ConstantInt *FB = EndPoints[0]; 0
1226 ConstantInt *FE = EndPoints[1]; 0
1227 if (tryMergeRange(EndPoints, FB, FE)) { 0
1228 for (unsigned i = 0; i < Size - 2; ++i) { 0
1229 EndPoints[i] = EndPoints[i + 2]; 0
1230 } ----
1231 EndPoints.resize(Size - 2); 0
1232 } ----
1233 } ----
1234 ----
1235 // If in the end we have a single range, it is possible that it is now the ----
1236 // full range. Just drop the metadata in that case. ----
1237 if (EndPoints.size() == 2) { 0
1238 ConstantRange Range(EndPoints[0]->getValue(), EndPoints[1]->getValue()); 0
1239 if (Range.isFullSet()) 0
1240 return nullptr; 0
1241 } 0
1242 ----
1243 SmallVector MDs; 0
1244 MDs.reserve(EndPoints.size()); 0
1245 for (auto *I : EndPoints) 0
1246 MDs.push_back(ConstantAsMetadata::get(I)); 0
1247 return MDNode::get(A->getContext(), MDs); 0
1248 } 0
1249 ----
1250 MDNode *MDNode::getMostGenericAlignmentOrDereferenceable(MDNode *A, MDNode *B) { 0
1251 if (!A || !B) 0
1252 return nullptr; 0
1253 ----
1254 ConstantInt *AVal = mdconst::extract(A->getOperand(0)); 0
1255 ConstantInt *BVal = mdconst::extract(B->getOperand(0)); 0
1256 if (AVal->getZExtValue() < BVal->getZExtValue()) 0
1257 return A; 0
1258 return B; 0
1259 } ----

1391 void Value::setMetadata(unsigned KindID, MDNode *Node) { 14 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll

1393 ----
1394 // Handle the case when we're adding/updating metadata on a value. ----
1395 if (Node) { 14 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1396 auto &Info = getContext().pImpl->ValueMetadata[this]; 0
1397 assert(!Info.empty() == HasMetadata && "bit out of sync with hash table"); 0

1404 // Otherwise, we're removing metadata from an instruction. ----
1405 assert((HasMetadata == (getContext().pImpl->ValueMetadata.count(this) > 0)) && 14 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1406 "bit out of sync with hash table"); ----
1407 if (!HasMetadata) 14 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1408 return; // Nothing to remove! 14 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1409 auto &Info = getContext().pImpl->ValueMetadata[this]; 0
